# AWS S3 Data Encryption

## What I did:

- Enabled default encryption for S3 bucket
- Configured server-side encryption (SSE-S3)
- Verified encryption settings

---

## Key Learnings:

- Encryption protects data at rest
- AWS provides built-in encryption mechanisms
- Encryption is essential for compliance and security

---

## Hands-on Summary:

- Enabled SSE-S3 encryption
- Ensured all new objects are encrypted automatically

---

## Mistakes to Avoid:

- Storing sensitive data without encryption
- Ignoring compliance requirements
- Not verifying encryption settings

---

## Security Insight:

- Encryption reduces risk of data exposure
- Even if data is accessed, it remains protected

